critique: This executive order deals with land use and resource management, specifically modifying previous orders related to land in Oregon. It authorizes the Secretary of the Interior to withdraw land for use by the Department of Commerce for air navigation facilities. It also references existing power transmission line reservations and timber sales. Given the nature of the document, it has limited implications for most of the axes. It doesn't directly address immigration, executive power in a broad sense, federalism, national security vs. civil liberties, or social inclusion. The primary areas where it has some relevance are economic regulation and ideological tilt, although even there, the impact is minimal.
